The paper deals with the stretch factor of Delaunay triangulations, which is a fundamental topic in computational geometry. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, graph theory, and optimization, which are typical of the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which are relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results and applications, which are relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Overall, cs.CG and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DM, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
